					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9781996#post-4104713</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-9781996/scp-4146#post-4104713</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 31 Dec 2018 23:43:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>The Great Hippo</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3938622</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I agree with Pedantique and mlister upthread; the expunged seems a little 'meh', and the formatting of the document (<em>grunts with pain</em> just inserted with no symbols to differentiate it from spoken text; lack of line-breaks between lines) is a little off.</p> <p>But the rest of the skip is excellent, both in concept and execution; the babbling is evocative both of the time period and of the real life occurrence of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dutch_Schultz#Last_words_and_posthumous_events">Dutch Schultz</a>. I kind of wish it had gone on for just a smidge <em>longer</em>, maybe &#8212; but the briefness is appreciated.</p> <p><strong>ETA:</strong> Particularly liked &quot;Chappy&quot; for &quot;Chapelle&quot;.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
